Corporate Profile
Background

			Established in 1962, ArcBest Technologies is a wholly-owned subsidiary of ArcBest CorporationSM, 
			a transportation focused enterprise headquartered in Fort Smith, Arkansas. ArcBest Technologies' role is developing 
			and supporting applications for the other subsidiaries in the ArcBest corporate family. We 
			play an integral part in helping the other subsidiaries achieve their goals by providing 
			innovative and up-to-date information technology solutions to the business challenges they face. 
			ArcBest Technologies also provides comprehensive information services to a select group of non-corporate clients.
		


			The largest subsidiary in the corporate family is ABF FreightSM, 
			a Fortune 1000 transportation and logistics supplier who has been recognized by receiving several awards of 
			excellence. ABF Freight is the only six-time winner of the American Trucking Associations President�s Trophy for Safety 
			and the only six-time winner of the Excellence in Security Award. ABF Freight also is the only carrier to earn both the
			Excellence in Claims/Loss Prevention Award and the Excellence in Security Award in the same year,
			which ABF Freight accomplished twice. In 2009, for the eighth consecutive year, ABF Freight was ranked among the
			top 10 of Selling Power magazine�s listing of the 25 best U.S. companies to sell for in the service
			sector. ABF Freight was again the highest-ranking transportation company on the magazine�s 2009 listing.
			In 2012 ABF Freight was also named one of Training magazine�s Training Top 125 for the third consecutive year.
			ABF Freight ranked seventh on the list.
		
Vision

			The vision of ArcBest Technologies is to be a highly effective and respected Information 
			Technology services provider.  The mission is to provide quality services in a 
			cost-effective manner.  To accomplish this, ArcBest Technologies provides an outstanding 
			hardware and system software environment, one that has both the capacity and robustness 
			needed by a major transportation company.  ArcBest Technologies next focuses on providing 
			excellent custom-developed software solutions that address the unique needs of 
			ABF Freight and the other subsidiaries of ArcBest Corporation.  And finally, ArcBest Technologies insures 
			that access to its systems is fast, efficient, and secure, utilizing the latest in system 
			protection mechanisms and procedures.  ArcBest Technologies appreciates the strategic nature 
			of Information Technology in business today and aims to provide not only technically 
			effective applications but also  applications that add genuine value to the overall business.
		
Our Role

			Today over 300 employees of ArcBest Technologies provide a variety of services throughout the 
			corporation and its other clients. Their primary function is designing, programming, 
			and maintaining business application systems. Applications are developed for Internet, 
			mainframe, client/server, and personal computer environments.
		

			Applications include:
			
General business
Customer freight management 
Human resources 
				Inventory management and control 
Production control and demand forecasting 
Equipment control and maintenance 
Logistics 
Imaging 
Freight billing, rating, pricing, and movement control 
Management information reporting 
Mobile computing systems 
Barcoding
Electronic data interchange 
Voice response systems 








CAREERS

Learn more about the career opportunities at ArcBest Technologies.



